            <!-- Left Side Element -->
            <a href="#hero" class="nav-logo">Whispers<span>.</span></a>
            
            <!-- Right Side Element -->
            <ul class="nav-links">
                <li><a href="#story">Story</a></li>
                <li><a href="#characters">Characters</a></li>
                <li><a href="#chapters">Chapters</a></li>
                <li><a href="#quotes">Quotes</a></li>
                <li><a href="#journey">Journey</a></li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </nav>

    <!-- HERO SECTION (SPLIT TWO-COLUMN LAYOUT) -->
    <header id="hero">
        <div class="hero-container">
            <!-- Left Side Content Column -->
            <div class="hero-content">
                <h1 class="hero-title">Whispers in the Dark</h1>
                <div class="hero-author">Deva Harsha V</div>
                
                <h2 class="hero-tagline">"The best ghosts are the ones who walk in daylight."</h2>
                <p class="hero-hook">A severed head in the murky deep of Cooum Lake sparks a chilling investigation that resurrects the ghosts of a long-buried dark ritualistic past.</p>
                
                <a href="#story" class="scroll-indicator">
                    <span>Begin the Descent</span>
                    <div class="scroll-line"></div>
                </a>
            </div>

            <!-- Right Side Poster Column -->
            <div class="hero-cover-side">
                <div class="cover-wrapper">
                    <div class="book-cover" style="background: url('https://cdn-gcs.inkitt.com/vertical_storycovers/b0793b665a152f52749ee32e2fdb24ec.jpg') center/cover no-repeat;"></div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </header>

    <!-- STORY SECTION -->
    <section id="story">
        <span class="section-label">The Dossier</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">The Case File</h2>
        
        <div class="story-grid">
            <div class="story-left">
                <div class="story-highlight-quote">
                    "Surgical-level precision in dismemberment. No sign of jagged tearing or panic. Killer likely used medical-grade tools. Clean. Professional. Cold."
                </div>
                <div class="story-narrative">
                    <p>What begins as a crisp, pre-dawn charity marathon in Chennai turns into a grotesque public circus when a scrawny student accidentally uncovers a waterlogged severed human head. As diving units comb the depths of Cooum Lake, plastic bags stitched with immaculate surgical discipline emerge, revealing a puzzle of body parts and a perfectly preserved heart.</p>
                    <p>Assigned to the real-world horrors of the Chennai division, four brilliant Central Bureau of Investigation interns are tested under extreme structural pressure. They quickly connect the grim signature to the legendary 'Anandi' serial killings that paralyzed Coimbatore twenty years prior. But back then, the victims were strictly women—and the killer was presumed dead, swallowed by the jungle.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="themes-wrapper">
                    <h3 class="themes-heading">Core Motifs</h3>
                    <div class="theme-tags">
                        <span class="theme-tag">Vengeance vs. Justice</span>
                        <span class="theme-tag">Clinical Vigilantism</span>
                        <span class="theme-tag">Cyber-Forensic Frameworks</span>
                        <span class="theme-tag">The Trauma of Birth</span>
                        <span class="theme-tag">The Fractured Fourth Wall</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <aside class="stats-sidebar">
                <div class="stat-card">
                    <div class="stat-value">Thriller</div>
                    <div class="stat-label">Genre</div>
                </div>
                <div class="stat-card">
                    <div class="stat-value">5</div>
                    <div class="stat-label">Investigated Chapters</div>
                </div>
                <div class="stat-card">
                    <div class="stat-value">22 Years</div>
                    <div class="stat-label">Timeline Timespan</div>
                </div>
                <div class="stat-card">
                    <div class="stat-value">4</div>
                    <div class="stat-label">CBI Intern Intellects</div>
                </div>
            </aside>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CHARACTERS SECTION -->
    <section id="characters">
        <span class="section-label">Personnel Data</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">The Profiles</h2>
        
        <div class="characters-grid">
            <!-- Character 1 -->
            <div class="character-card">
                <div class="char-header">
                    <h3 class="char-name">Vishnu Kumar</h3>
                    <div class="char-role">The Ghost in the System</div>
                </div>
                <p class="char-desc">An elusive civilian tech analyst who pioneered India's earliest GPS crime patterning software. Weathered, sharp-eyed, and clinical, he possesses an uncanny psychological alignment with the killer's internal framework. He walked away from the system—yet his shadows run deep.</p>
                <div class="traits-container">
                    <span class="trait-badge">Methodical</span>
                    <span class="trait-badge">Brilliant</span>
                    <span class="trait-badge">Haunted</span>
                    <span class="trait-badge">Vigilante</span>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Character 2 -->
            <div class="character-card">
                <div class="char-header">
                    <h3 class="char-name">ACP Rajan</h3>
                    <div class="char-role">The Old Guard</div>
                </div>
                <p class="char-desc">A retired, battle-scarred veteran of the police department who stood second-in-command during the original 2003 hunt. Imposing and deeply protective of his past and his family, he remains permanently altered by the horrific memories of Anandi's gaze.</p>
                <div class="traits-container">
                    <span class="trait-badge">Stern</span>
                    <span class="trait-badge">Guarded</span>
                    <span class="trait-badge">Protective</span>
                    <span class="trait-badge">Regretful</span>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Character 3 -->
            <div class="character-card">
                <div class="char-header">
                    <h3 class="char-name">Anandi / Nanda</h3>
                    <div class="char-role">The Midwife of Death</div>
                </div>
                <p class="char-desc">Once a village midwife who witnessed systemic atrocities, her mind cracked beneath the weight of silent horrors. Operating under complex surgical delusions, she targets medical personnel who she believes failed their sacred maternal duties, posing her victims like sleeping newborns.</p>
                <div class="traits-container">
                    <span class="trait-badge">Calculated</span>
                    <span class="trait-badge">Surgical</span>
                    <span class="trait-badge">Zealot</span>
                    <span class="trait-badge">Presumed Dead</span>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Character 4 -->
            <div class="character-card">
                <div class="char-header">
                    <h3 class="char-name">The Intern Core</h3>
                    <div class="char-role">CBI Cold Pattern Subunit</div>
                </div>
                <p class="char-desc">Composed of Nikhil (forensic specialist), Maya (hyper-retentive digital archivist), Aarav (data architect), and Diya (observant analyst and Rajan’s daughter). Together, they parse through the decay of ancient file rooms to locate the anomalies of the present case.</p>
                <div class="traits-container">
                    <span class="trait-badge">Analytical</span>
                    <span class="trait-badge">Tenacious</span>
                    <span class="trait-badge">Vulnerable</span>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CHAPTERS SECTION -->
    <section id="chapters">
        <span class="section-label">Manifest</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">The Chronology</h2>
        
        <div class="chapters-grid">
            <div class="chapter-card">
                <span class="ch-num">Chapter 1</span>
                <h3 class="ch-title">The Bag in the Lake</h3>
                <p class="ch-teaser">A crisp morning marathon in Chennai devolves into chaos as an unexpected accident reveals a macabre underwater tomb within Cooum Lake.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="chapter-card">
                <span class="ch-num">Chapter 2</span>
                <h3 class="ch-title">Four Young Minds</h3>
                <p class="ch-teaser">Inside the CBI war room in New Delhi, an elite intern squad unearths a closed file from 2003, connecting the present horror to a terrifying ghost M.O.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="chapter-card">
                <span class="ch-num">Chapter 3</span>
                <h3 class="ch-title">Names from the Dust</h3>
                <p class="ch-teaser">Deep within the damp basement archives of Chennai HQ, a private audio tape of Anandi's final interrogation reawakens forgotten sins.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="chapter-card">
                <span class="ch-num">Chapter 4</span>
                <h3 class="ch-title">The Visitors</h3>
                <p class="ch-teaser">The past walks through the front door at Rajan's house as Vishnu Kumar steps out of the shadows to reconstruct the bloody inception of 2003.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="chapter-card">
                <span class="ch-num">Chapter 5</span>
                <h3 class="ch-title">First Blood</h3>
                <p class="ch-teaser">The flashback intensifies in Coimbatore. A nurse is discovered in a sanitation pit with a stitched silence, sending shockwaves through the community.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- QUOTES SECTION -->
    <section id="quotes">
        <span class="section-label">Audio Intercepts</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">The Echoes</h2>
        
        <div class="quotes-container">
            <div class="featured-quote-box">
                <span class="quote-icon">“</span>
                <p class="featured-quote-text">"Because women birth monsters. And sometimes... they are monsters."</p>
                <div class="featured-quote-author">Anandi — Case Interrogation Tape</div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="quotes-subgrid">
                <div class="quote-card">
                    <p class="quote-card-text">"I do not kill out of hate. I kill to cleanse. If you use your freedom to betray, to murder silently... You are a woman. You are a wound."</p>
                    <div class="quote-card-author">The Red Diary Page 10</div>
                </div>
                <div class="quote-card">
                    <p class="quote-card-text">"She didn't just kill. She wanted to rebirth the world she thought was unjust."</p>
                    <div class="quote-card-author">Vishnu Kumar</div>
                </div>
                <div class="quote-card">
                    <p class="quote-card-text">"The best ghosts are the ones who walk in daylight."</p>
                    <div class="quote-card-author">The Archives</div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- JOURNEY / TIMELINE SECTION -->
    <section id="journey">
        <span class="section-label">Temporal Record</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">The Path of Decay</h2>
        
        <div class="timeline-container">
            <!-- Event 1 -->
            <div class="timeline-item">
                <div class="timeline-node"></div>
                <div class="timeline-meta">June 1987 — The Genesis</div>
                <h3 class="timeline-heading">Tradition of Silence</h3>
                <p class="timeline-body">Anandi serves as a rural midwife, forced to participate in the hushed execution of newborn daughters, planting the psychological seeds of a fractured narrative.</p>
            </div>
            
            <!-- Event 2 -->
            <div class="timeline-item">
                <div class="timeline-node"></div>
                <div class="timeline-meta">June 2003 — The First Sign</div>
                <h3 class="timeline-heading">The Irrigation Canal</h3>
                <p class="timeline-body">Schoolboys discover a woman tightly wrapped in white hospital-grade plastic, her limbs neatly curled into an eerie womb-like fetal form with her lips sewn shut.</p>
            </div>
            
            <!-- Event 3 -->
            <div class="timeline-item">
                <div class="timeline-node"></div>
                <div class="timeline-meta">August 2003 — Personal Escalation</div>
                <h3 class="timeline-heading">Shadows Hit Home</h3>
                <p class="timeline-body">Vishnu's own sister, an MBBS intern harboring hidden trauma, is targeted and discovered inside a maintenance shed, transforming the case into a direct personal vendetta.</p>
            </div>
            
            <!-- Event 4 -->
            <div class="timeline-item">
                <div class="timeline-node"></div>
                <div class="timeline-meta">Late August 2003 — The Cliff Edge</div>
                <h3 class="timeline-heading">The Western Ghats</h3>
                <p class="timeline-body">A reckless manhunt culminates at a forgotten, rain-slicked maternity center. Nanda slips through Vishnu's fingers, falling off a steep cliff into raging river waters; no body is ever recovered.</p>
            </div>
            
            <!-- Event 5 -->
            <div class="timeline-item">
                <div class="timeline-node"></div>
                <div class="timeline-meta">Present Day (2025) — The Counterpoint</div>
                <h3 class="timeline-heading">The Lake of Limbs</h3>
                <p class="timeline-body">The identical surgical pattern returns in Chennai, but the core formula undergoes a terrifying deviation: the latest dismembered victim is completely male.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ENDING SECTION -->
    <section id="ending">
        <span class="section-label">Final Transmission</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">The Illusion Broken</h2>
        <p class="ending-message">The interns step back out into the humid Chennai night, sensing that the immaculate alignment of the new murder is too perfect to be an ordinary imitation. The mystery does not rest in the history archives—it sits across the table from them.</p>
        <div class="ending-quote-box">
            "You don't know the full story yet."
        </div>
        <p class="ending-reflection">A quiet lakeside. A figure dressed in black. Pushing a second bundle into the dark waters. The cycle hasn't repeated... it has simply been taken over.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- FOOTER -->
    <footer>
        <div class="footer-title">Whispers in the Dark</div>
        <span class="footer-author">Deva Harsha V © 2025</span>
        <p class="footer-quote">"He turned his head. And looked straight through the fourth wall—at us."</p>
    </footer>

    <!-- INTERACTIVE SCROLL SCRIPT -->
    <script>
        document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
            const sections = document.querySelectorAll('section, header');
            const navLinks = document.querySelectorAll('.nav-links a');

            window.addEventListener('scroll', () => {
                let current = '';
                
                sections.forEach(section => {
                    const sectionTop = section.offsetTop;
                    const sectionHeight = section.clientHeight;
                    if (pageYOffset >= (sectionTop - sectionHeight / 3)) {
                        current = section.getAttribute('id');
                    }
                });

                navLinks.forEach(link => {
                    link.classList.remove('active');
                    if (link.getAttribute('href').slice(1) === current) {
                        link.classList.add('active');
                    }
                });
            });
        });
    </script>
    <%- include('partials/footer') %>